products.title: Chicken CSA 6 months
products.body_html:
If you love high quality pastured chicken and want to gain access to it regularly at a discount, consider our Just Chicken CSA. Community Supported Agriculture is a program where eaters can enjoy discounted but consistent access to the best of what's coming off of a farm in exchange for paying partially up front. Our just chicken CSA will run for six months and will include whole chickens and/or chicken cuts monthly, depending on which package you choose. You win with our chicken CSA because you won't need to buy a new freezer to get a discount or to avoid finding that your favorites have gone out of stock.

We call our chicken "actually free range" because the animal husbandry practices of our chicken raising system go well above and beyond the standards of "free range" and "pastured" systems. Our chickens enjoy fresh non-GMO feed and freedom in wide-open pastures for most of their lives on our farm. This mean that our chickens do plenty of foraging in our lush diverse pastures full of clover, grass and bugs. More time and space for foraging means more flavor and nutrients in your chicken; Not to mention happier chickens, and healthier land, air, and water.

As always, our animals are never fed genetically modified organisms. They are bred to thrive outdoors, and do live their lives outdoors, roaming and foraging from our fresh rotating pastures and forests. 

We pledge to make sure that each month you receive 20% more chicken than you would if you spent the same amount at our retail booth. We offer three sizes to choose from, priced at $45, $70, and $120 per month. Feel free to pay all up front or pay half up front.  The other half will be split up between the six monthly pickups. 

NEW!: We are also now offering a All Chicken Cuts offering for those who would prefer to not work with whole birds. (details below) 

Bundle Options:

Two whole chickens totaling about 8.5 lbs: $45/month: 

Two chickens totaling about 8.5 lbs and about two packs of chicken cuts: $70/month: 

Four Chickens totaling about 17 lbs and 3-4 packs of chicken cuts: $120/month:

All Chicken Cuts!: You pick each month: Breast, thigh, drum, wing, soup bones, organs. $80/ month gets you $93 worth of chicken cuts!

Below is our regular CSA schedule, however the days and times will remain subject to change.

Pick up locations (subject to change):

-Second Saturday of the month, 8 AM - NOON  (10-Noon from Dec-March). The Original Bardstown Road Farmers Market: 1722 Bardstown Road, Louisville, KY

-Second Tuesday of the month at 1:00 PM: Sojourn Community Church: 2023 Ekin Ave, New Albany, IN 47150 

-Second Tuesday of the month at 3:30 PM: Lakshmi Farms in Anchorage KY: 12400 Lucas Ln, Louisville, KY 40223

-Fourth Saturday of the month, 8 AM - NOON. The Original Bardstown Road Farmers Market: 1722 Bardstown Road, Louisville, KY. 

-Second Tuesday of the month, HOME DELIVERY to Jefferson and Oldham county, KY, Floyd and Clark county, IN. (Fee is $10 per delivery) 

-Monthly pickup in Indianapolis at Tallow Skin Balm co.

The Chicken CSA program is available year-round, and runs for six months, beginning with the next available delivery or pick-up.

2 (12 oz.) Bone-in Ribeye Steaks

(2.5 lbs) Beef Stew Meat
(Approx 3 lb) Short Ribs

13 (1 lb. pkgs.) Ground Beef

Hot Dogs & Picnic Fare:
12 (3.5 oz.) All-Beef Nitrate-free Franks
2 (16 oz. pkgs.) Beef Bologona

(Optional) Organs and Bones:

Select "organs and bones" option, and we'll throw in 1+ lbs of beef liver, one package of beef heart, 3+ lbs of of shank or soup bones, and two pounds of our primal ground beef (containing 25% liver and heart and 75% ground beef)!


We've included a variety of juicy steaks, dogs and burgers that are perfect for the grill, and you'll have plenty of ground beef to stock the freezer for chili, tacos, burgers, spaghetti and more. And the slow-cooker lover will be covered with hearty roasts and stew meat. Lastly, we've included two of our all-beef MSG-free Bologna! These firm, smoked, ready-to-eat sausages are perfect for a picnic, sandwiches, or a charcuterie board.

The Groce Family Farm 1/8th Beef Box is perfect for individuals or families who need help meal planning or are serious about eating nutrient-packed pasture beef throughout the week.

Our animals are 100% grass-fed and raised with great care, rotating to fresh pastures each day. If you're looking to stock up on beef, the 1/8 Beef Box is your best bet.

products.title: Monthly Super Simple Meat CSA
products.body_html:
NEW: A CSA offering for the most discerning/restrictive diets

Since 2017, our CSA (Community Supported Agriculture)subscription program has provided a wide variety of meats to hundreds of families throughout Kentuckiana who want confidence in the integrity of their meats. We work with a hand full of butchers in the area to add in their skill and resources to our work so that we can provide the best tasting products with the cleanest labels possible. Along the way though, we've run into folks looking to eliminate even small amounts of things like sugar, nitrates, or label terms such as "spices", which leave some ambiguity. 

So now we are offering a similar monthly variety bundle. But instead of including the widest variety of sausages, cured meats, and brats, we're offering a CSA with just plain ground products and whole-tissue meat.  

This, and all our Community Supported Agriculture Program members can rely upon us for:

  • Discounted but consistent access to the best pastured meats.
  • Wide variety of pasture raised chicken turkey and pork; and grass fed beef.
  • Convenient monthly drop-off locations.
  • NOW OFFERING home delivery option!
  • No need to buy a new freezer to get a discount or to avoid having your favorites go out of stock.
  • Each month receive at least 20% more than if you spent the same amount at our retail booth.
  • Three sizes to choose from: priced at $90, $120, and $165 per month.
  • You eat every day. So our CSA program is available year-round! Start anytime for six or twelve months.

What is included?:  

  • Economy ($90/month): 1 small whole chicken, 1.5 lbs chicken breast, 2 (1+lb) packages of chicken dark meat, 1 lb ground beef, 1 lb ground poultry (chicken or turkey) 1.5-3 lbs red meat (i.e. pork chops, beef roast, steaks or ribs)
  • Family ($120/month): 1 medium whole chicken, 2.5 lbs chicken breast, 2 (1+lb) packages of chicken dark meat, 2 lb ground beef, 1 lb ground poultry (chicken or turkey) 2-4 lbs red meat (i.e. pork chops, beef roast, steaks or ribs)
  • Big Eater (approx. 20-25 lbs meat for $165/month): 1 large whole chicken, 3 lbs chicken breast, 3 (1+lb) packages of chicken dark meat, 3 lb ground beef, 1 lb ground poultry (chicken or turkey) 3-5 lbs red meat (i.e. pork chops, beef roast, steaks or ribs)

 

As always, our animals are never fed genetically modified organisms. They are bred to thrive where they live, outdoors roaming and foraging from our fresh rotating pastures and forests. Our lamb and cattle diet is 100% forage: just grass and other pasture plants, no grain. For more about how we raise our products, click here. But in short, you can feel confident that animal welfare, land stewardship. flavor, and human health are all maximized because of our farming practices.
